node.title: NT records one new COVID case as source of current outbreak remains unknown
node.alt: Michael Gunner talks at COVID presser.
node.description: The Northern Territory records one new case of coronavirus, a 21-year old woman who recently arrived in Darwin from Cairns, onÂ day two of lockdown restrictions in Katherine and a lockout in Greater Darwin.
node.content:
["The Northern Territory has recorded one new case of coronavirus,\u00a0Chief Minister Michael Gunner\u00a0says.", "The new case is a\u00a021-year old woman who arrived in Darwin from Cairns on Friday, October 29.", "She is a\u00a0close contact of\u00a0the initial case in the current outbreak, which has now grown to three cases.", "She was identified as a close contact yesterday and was moved to the Howard Springs quarantine\u00a0facility, where she tested positive late last night.", "Mr Gunner said the woman, who has\u00a0received one dose of the vaccine, became symptomatic today.", "He said she was being interviewed, and contact tracing had commenced.", "\"There may be more exposure sites for Darwin, so it is critical that everybody in the Top End pay very careful attention to these and look for updates throughout the day,\" Mr Gunner said.", "\"We will communicate these as soon as we can.\"", "All exposure sites and testing and isolation directions can be found on the NT government's coronavirus\u00a0website.", "On Thursday Katherine was sent into lockdown and it was announced Greater Darwin\u00a0would be subject to the NT's first \"lockout\" after\u00a0an unvaccinated man in his 20s tested positive.", "On Friday a\u00a0second\u00a0positive COVID case,\u00a0an unvaccinated\u00a055-year-old man,\u00a0was detected in Katherine.", "The initial case is considered the Northern Territory's first case of community transmission.", "Mr Gunner said the source of the infection remained unknown.", "The lockdown in Katherine and lockout in Greater Darwin are scheduled to end at midnight on Sunday.", "", "
